
[1]pious

   PI'OUS, a. [L. pius.]

   1. Godly; reverencing and honoring the Supreme Being in heart and in
   the practice of the duties he has enjoined; having due veneration and
   affection for the character of God, and habitually obeying his
   commands; religious; devoted to the service of God; applied to persons.

   2. Dictated by reverence to God; proceeding from piety; applied to
   things; as pious awe; pious services of affections; pious sorrow.

   3. Having due respect and affection for parents or other relatives;
   practicing the duties of respect and affection towards parents or other
   near relatives.

   4. Practiced under the pretense of religion; as pious frauds.
